8/9/00
  Time base offset adjustment:
      - time base change in source: abrupt, big change
      - drift due to clock mismatch: slow and small change
      Only adjust time base offset when change is above a threshold!

  When time base offset is adjusted, do we need to recalculate timestamp?

  There are two ways to map PTS/DTS:
    - based on original PTS/DTS and time base offset 
    - based on time base regeneration
  Which one to pick if there is big difference between the two approach?


