8/14/00
  Weekend test result: PPC stop responding in less than 20 min!
                       Picture still there, but keeps on breaking up.

  Found a potential bug in statmux with Matt:
    PCR drift distribtuion code may not work at low output rate.
    The measured PCR drift is to be distributed to output at small chunks.
    Each chunk is 1/64 of the drift.  If the number of chunk pre quarter sec
    is less than 64, we may not adjust enough!
  Matt verified that this is not the problem.
  However, it seems to us now that the DPI is already doing drift correction
  by time base mapping.  The tbOffset actuall contains both the phase change
  and drift.  Matt is trying to turn off drift correction in Mux to see
  whether it works.

  New splice algorithm work:
    Moved to anchor unit based passing.
    Trying to remove pendingPts flag and use anchor PTS regeneration
    when anchor unit is completed, if necessary.


