8/25/00

  Issues:

    - Splice control task runs too often in SUN simulation.
      Add task Delay to slow down.
      DONE

    - Leading B picture dropping
      Modify entryCandidateFound() to consider the closedGop flag to determine
      achor unit's start time:  (closedGop? refPicStat->det : refPicStat->pts)
      Then in procBgSeekChan(), drop the leading B picture if entry candidate
      found and !closedGop.
      DONE

    - start/stop/fill time updating and freezing scheme
      - dropAnchorUnit() updates all times
      - passAnchorUnit() updates stop/fill times
      - black picture insertion / fill channel routines update fill time
      - procExitPoint() freezes FG stop time
      - procEntryPoint() freezes FG fill time and BG start time

      Note: FG fill time = BG start time
            tsDelay = FG stop time - BG start time
      DONE

    - channel end point determination
      Output task updates a new variable lastOutPicCnt after outputing a picture
      (copied its inPicCnt).
      (In non-seamless splicing, inPicCnt is set back and reused to fill picture
       generation.)
      Output task will no longer check for channel end point.  May get rid of
      endPicStat.
      Splice control task will do the comparison between lastOutPicCnt and inPicCnt
      to determine videoDone.  If audio and vbi are also done, then issue
      the splice inidcation to PPC directly.  I.e., no longer do output task
      and audio/vbi task need to send semaphore to splice control task!!
      Need a complete redesign of splice control task!
      DONE

    - Sequence end code insertion scheme
      A quick and dirty way is to add sequence/GOP headers and sequence end code
      to every black/fill/glue pictures.

      Better approach:
        - Always put sequence end code at last FG picture (if needed)
        - Only put sequence end cod at last black picture, right before the first
          BG frame.
      Whenever insertPostBlack() or fillChan() are called, it will generate a
      bunch of black 2-field pictures, will sequence/GOP header in first picture.
      In insertPostBlack(), we try to sent one frame less than the request number
      of postBlack.
      Then when procEntryPoint() is called, it will insert one more black frame
      if:
        - postBlack > 0, to make up the missing frame and to close sequence, or
        - blackPicCnt > 0, to close sequence, or
        - field parity conflict found
      This also means that the maxTsDelay can be MAX_TS_DELAY + 3 field time. 

    - Simplify all done flags
      Instead of using individual done flags for video, audio and vbi, we simply
      add a variable in SwitchReq which stores the number of PidChans not
      ready for switch.  Then when this variable count down to zero, it is
      ready for switch.


